So hashcat will automatically call all available GPUs, so there’s nothing you need to configure on your side. The timeout that occurred is simply because your GPU struggled with the difficulty of the challenge. As Lucian mentioned, if you upgrade to a multi-GPU system, you’ll be in a better position to solve higher-difficulty challenges. Regarding the wandb error that posted, that’s because wandb imposes rate-limiting on their free accounts. It’s an issue everyone has and nothing to worry about for now.

If you’re going to use multiple GPUs, you’re best off configuring the new machine first (I recommend the best interconnect you can find). After it’s set up and tested to work, kill the miner process on your first machine and start it on the second machine in order to have the smallest downtime possible.
